HEADWORD: BWR
<hw>BWR</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a boiling water reactor; a type of
nuclear reactor that uses water as a coolant and moderator; -- the steam
produced can drive a steam turbine and produce electrical
power.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> boiling water reactor.</syn>⟦br⟧
